$ SQL Server: variables

Variables are declared with the → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables/declare[`declare` statement] which associates the variable with a
→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types[data type].

Values are assigned to variables with either the
  • → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/set/assign-variables[`set` statement] or the
  • → development/databases/SQL-Server/sql/select/assign-variables[SQL `select` statement].

{ Scope

  The scope of a variable does not extend over multiple → development/databases/SQL-Server/sql/batch[batches].

}

sa:
  Some »predefined« → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables/atat[variables that start with `@@`]

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL
